Put a large #pot{} of water on to boil with a @salt{pinch}. Chop the @purple potato{2} into roughly 2cm chunks (no need to peel). Once the water is boiling, pop your potato into the pot and cook for ~{15%minutes} or until your potato is cooked.

> The potato is cooked when you can easily slip a knife through.

Once cooked, drain and pop back into the pot with the lid on. Pre-heat your #oven{} to 200 degrees.

Cut the bottom and the top 2cm off the @leek{2}. Cut in half lengthways then slice into 1cm wide half moons. Separate the @flat leaf parsley{1} leaves from their stalks. Roughly chop the leaves and finely chop the stalks. Drain and rinse the @sweetcorn{1} in a #sieve{} or #colander{}. Boil your #kettle{}.

Put a large #frying pan{} or wide bottomed #saucepan{} on medium heat with a drizzle of oil and add your leek along with a pinch of salt and a grind of @black pepper{}. Cook for ~{6-7%minutes} until soft (if it browns slightly, don't worry, this will just add to the flavour!). Once your leek is soft, add your sweetcorn and parsley leaves and stir together. Cook for a further ~{2%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat.

Pour boiling water from the kettle (amount specified in the ingredient list) into a #measuring jug{} and add the @fish stock pot{1}. Stir to dissolve.

Add the @creme fraiche{1} to your leek and sweetcorn and mix well. Add your stock, and stir everything together.

Put your @smoked fish mix{425%g} in the bottom of an #ovenproof dish{} and spoon your veggies on top (include any excess sauce).

When your potato is drained and back in the pot, add your parsley stalks, @Netherend butter salted{30%g} and a splash of milk (if you have some) along with some salt and pepper. Mash until smooth with a #potato masher{}.

Layer your mashed potato on top your veggies and flatten it out. Using a #fork{}, make lines in the top of the pie (see picture).

> This will give you some crispy edges.

Cook your fish pie in your oven for ~{15%minutes}, then turn your #grill{} to high and place underneath, until the top is slightly crispy.

> The fish is cooked when opaque and flaky. While your pie is cooking, do your washing up!

When cooked, spoon your fish pie into bowls and devour!